Template: automation-interface-mta/choose_smtp_proto
Type: multiselect
Choices: smtp, authsmtp, no configuration
Description: Choose between plain smtp and smtp auth (tls)
  Choose smtp send protocol


Template: automation-interface-mta/from
Type: string
Description: Insert the sender mail address
  Mail From

Template: automation-interface-mta/to
Type: string
Description: Insert the recipient mail address
  Mail TO

Template: automation-interface-mta/relay
Type: string
Description: Insert the hostname of the relay host
  Relay host

Template: automation-interface-mta/allowed_net
Type: string
Description: Insert the subnet from which accept messages (usually this is the containers's subnet)
  Allowed subnet

Template: automation-interface-mta/username
Type: string
Description: Insert the username for the relay host
  Smtp auth username

Template: automation-interface-mta/password
Type: password
Description: Insert the password for the relay host
  Smtp auth password

Template: automation-interface-mta/tls
Type: string
Description: Insert the tls minimum version
  TLS version

Template: automation-interface-mta/tcp_port
Type: string
Description: Insert the tcp port for smtp auth
  Smtp auth tcp port

Template: automation-interface-mta/cert_file
Type: string
Description: Insert the path to the certficate file for smtp auth. Leave empty if no certificate was provided
  Cert file

Template: automation-interface-mta/key_file
Type: string
Description: Insert the path to the key file for smtp auth. Leave empty if no key was provided.
  Key file
